reviewText: I liked watching this show on tv and I'm so glad that they came out with the episodes on dvd. Commercial-Free too that's the best part and the dvd edition contains 6 episodes while the VHS only has 5 episodes. This is a great deal, it's like 132 mins long or something like that. It also includes never before seen bloopers, an interactive quiz, and a photo gallery. I would buy it now before it runs out. It's awesome Mary-Kate and Ashley Olsen are a lot more grown up and it makes the dvd worthwhile. Buy it now!

reviewText: The twinS growing up before our eyes.And what a great show So Little Time is..Appeals to all ages..My only complaint is where is the rest of this show..There are still 2 episodes missing from the dvds..Including my fav one where they play sick and then everyone gets sick for real.And there are about 3 unaired episodes.Its been almost a year since vol 4 hope they didn't forget.And the bloppers on here are HILARIOUS too.The character of Maneulo is classic tv comedy character.A laugh riot.And you get to see new sides to the Twins too including rocker metal girls in leather and wild hair just to name one (episode Girls just want to have fun).There are many suprises.A JOY all the way around.Get all of this show.Its one of the best shows in years.I also want to say where is TWO OF A KIND?? GET THIS YOU WON'T BE DISAPPIONTED AND GET OLSENIZED with so little time dvd serieS...
summary: TwinS Are Legends In Own Time But We Need More SoLittleTime
